# PocketForge WiFi credentials for the boot-resource FAT partition (A523 / tsp-s).
# Copy this file to wifi.txt and fill in your network details.
# wifi.txt is gitignored — it contains your WiFi password.
#
# In the hermetic `pf build --device a523 --artifact os-image` path, this file
# is not consumed from the checkout — pf-build.sh reads it from
# ~/.config/pocketforge/secrets/wifi/tsp-s and mounts it as a BuildKit secret;
# the assemble stage stages it into the FAT boot partition. See tsp-jet.4.
#
# Format: key=value, one per line. Comments (#) and blank lines are ok.
# Required: SSID, PSK
# Optional: KEY_MGMT  (default: WPA-PSK)
SSID=YourNetworkName
PSK=YourPassword
